Crowd sourced benchmarks from running the 'benchmarkme' package.

name: r-benchmarkmedata
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.0.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-benchmarkmedata
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/benchmarkmeData_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/benchmarkmeData/benchmarkmeData_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a8dacf85a1c548d011299dca78ec376a7fbea68d0b6482e763dca7685bad1417

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-tibble
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-tibble

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('benchmarkmeData')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('benchmarkmeData')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/csgillespie/benchmarkme-data
  license: GPL-2 | GPL-3
  license_file: {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3
  summary: Crowd sourced benchmarks from running the 'benchmarkme' package.
  license_family: GPL3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
